## <a id="lifecycle"></a>Lifecycle Management ##
Use these commands to manage releases, stemcells, and snapshots.

<table class="nice" >
  <tr>
    <th>Command</th>
    <th>Description</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>create release [MANIFEST_FILE] [--force] [--final] <br />[--with-tarball] [--dry-run] [--version VERSION]
</code></td>
	<td>
Creates a release.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>delete release NAME [VERSION] [--force]</code></td>
	<td>Deletes the release and associated jobs, packages, compiled packages, and their metadata. Fails if a deployment references this release.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>delete snapshot SNAPSHOT_CID</code></td>
	<td>Deletes a snapshot. Fails if the snapshot is in use.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>delete snapshots</code></td>
	<td>Deletes all snapshots.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>delete stemcell NAME VERSION [--force]</code></td>
	<td>Deletes a stemcell and all associated compiled packages. Fails if a deployment references this stemcell.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>download public stemcell STEMCELL_FILENAME</code></td>
	<td>Downloads the specified stemcell from the public blobstore.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>public stemcells [--full] [--all]</code></td>
	<td>Displays a list of public stemcells available for download.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>snapshots
</code></td>
	<td>Displays the job, CID, and created date of all snapshots.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>stemcells</code></td>
	<td>Displays the name, version, and CID of available stemcells.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>take snapshot [JOB] [INDEX]</code></td>
	<td>Takes a snapshot of the specified JOB VM.<br />
If the JOB is not specified, takes a snapshot of all deployments.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>upload release [RELEASE_FILE] [--rebase] [--skip-if-exists]</code></td>
	<td>Uploads the specified file as a release. If you do not provide a <code>RELEASE_FILE</code>, you must run this command from a valid release directory.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>upload stemcell STEMCELL_LOCATION [--skip-if-exists]
</code></td>
	<td>Uploads the specified stemcell. You must specify a URI if the <code>STEMCELL_LOCATION</code> is remote.</td>
  </tr>
</table>

